You create a managed solution in a development environment. The development environment contains new columns in the Account table that are used to store business-critical information.

You move the managed solution to the production environment and deploy an update to the solution.

A bug in the production environment is preventing users from updating account records.

You need to resolve the bug. The solution must minimize impact to the business and not create solution dependencies.

What should you do?

Select only one answer.

Apply the bug resolution to the managed solution in the production environment.

Uninstall the solution and then re-install the previous version.

Resolve the bug in the development environment and redeploy the solution.

Apply the bug resolution to a new unmanaged solution in the production environment.
